From 78ea40efb48e978756db2ce45fcfa55bac056b91 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Libin Yang <libin.yang@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Dec 2021 09:08:17 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: hda: intel-sdw-acpi: go through HDAS ACPI at max depth of 2
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 78ea40efb48e978756db2ce45fcfa55bac056b91
Patch-mainline: v5.16-rc7
References: git-fixes

In the HDAS ACPI scope, the SoundWire may not be the direct child of HDAS.
It needs to go through the ACPI table at max depth of 2 to find the
SoundWire device from HDAS.

